IO
==

Overview
--------
io/ contains only persistence classes and low-level private helper code.
The repo-wide module/data-flow diagram lives at docs/repo-internals.puml.

The classes form a simple chain:

  input ROOT files
      |
      v
  InputPartitionIO
      |
      v
  SampleIO
      |
      v
  DatasetIO
      |
      v
  EventListIO
      |
      v
  DistributionIO
      |
      v
  ChannelIO

More concretely:

  InputPartitionIO --scans--> one input file list / partition
  SampleIO         --builds--> one sample container from one or more partitions
  SampleIO         --exports-> DatasetIO::Sample metadata
  DatasetIO        --holds--> many named samples and their metadata
  EventListIO      --writes-> selected event trees and subrun trees
  DistributionIO   --writes-> binned distributions and persisted systematics payloads
  ChannelIO        --writes-> named channel/process bundles on common binning

Class notes
-----------
InputPartitionIO
  Small record for one partition of input ROOT files. It scans subruns, POT,
  and event counts and can write or read that partition summary.

SampleIO
  Builds a sample-level container from one or more InputPartitionIO
  partitions. It is the bridge between raw input lists and DatasetIO::Sample
  metadata.

DatasetIO
  Persistent collection of named samples. It stores sample metadata and sample
  provenance, but not selected event trees.

EventListIO
  Persistent analysis-ready output. It stores copied selected event trees,
  subrun trees, and sample metadata.
  Use it for row-wise analysis, event displays, and exploratory plotting.

DistributionIO
  Persistent bin-wise output. It stores binned distributions, statistical
  sumw2, and persisted systematic summaries derived from EventListIO.
  Use it for repeated plotting and other bin-wise downstream work.

ChannelIO
  Persistent assembled channel output. It stores one analysis region on common
  binning with many named processes, observed data bins, and per-process
  systematic payloads.
  Use it for stacked plots, fit-style exports, and final downstream channel
  views.

Private material
----------------
bits/
  Private helper code and schema notes used by io/ itself.

bits/NTUPLE
  Reference for the upstream input ntuple schema.

bits/DERIVED
  Reference for framework-owned derived columns and persisted EventListIO
  structure.
